  <div id="hdb" class="scroll-mt-40">
    <DefBox
      term="Keeping a Cavalier in an HDB flat"
      definition="The Cavalier King Charles Spaniel is named on the HDB-approved breed list, so you can keep one in an HDB flat. HDB allows one dog of an approved breed per flat, and the Cavalier's quiet, gentle indoor manner makes it one of the easiest approved breeds to live with in one. Every Cavalier we place has its dog licensing completed at purchase, so the paperwork is handled for you."
      bridge="Is a Cavalier HDB-approved? Yes, by name on the list. Just mind the one-dog-per-flat rule, and if you already have a dog, message us first so we can check your situation."
